KGA - one of my better games.

I used to have a lot of trouble with this defence - I would get myself in big trouble early by not developing pieces quickly enough.
I like this move.... it develops the B, prepares for castling and helps defend the centre. As you can see later, the black bishop plays a key role in tying up white's pieces
